##Shanghai's first case of Public Nuisance: defendant sentenced to eight months in prison

“

On the morning of February 21, the Shanghai Qingpu District People's Court adopted the Internet online trial mode in the second court of the court department and held a public hearing in accordance with the law. After verifying the facts and evidence of the case and hearing the views of all parties, the court found that the defendant's actions constituted a Obstruction of justice and sentenced the defendant to eight months'imprisonment.

”

At 9:15 am on February 21, the Shanghai Qingpu District People's Court adopted the Internet online trial mode in the second court of the court department and held a public hearing according to the law.

Since the Supreme People's Court, the Supreme People's Procuratorate, the Ministry of Public Security and the Ministry of Justice jointly issued the opinions on punishing according to law the illegal and criminal acts of preventing and controlling the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic on February 10, shanghai's first case involving epidemic prevention and control.

Earlier, the Minhang district People's Court on the morning of February 18 to open "cloud trial" of the first case in Shanghai for obstructing the anti-epidemic beating of volunteers involved in criminal cases.

On the afternoon of February 9, the defendant, surnamed Zhang, drove out with his family and returned to his residential area. Check the body temperature, security Wang found Zhang son temperature abnormalities, asked Zhang a family temporarily into the community, and in the second temperature normal to be released. Zhang therefore angry, refused to drive away and will be parked at the entrance to the residential area, resulting in other owners of vehicles can not pass. Shanghai Qingpu District Police Zhao arrived at the scene to give advice to Zhang and asked to cooperate with the epidemic prevention and control work, Zhang still refused to leave. After the police repeatedly warned, Zhang uses the point brake way to slowly move the vehicle. Subsequently, in the police to carry out mandatory away, Zhang suddenly accelerated driving, resulting in police arm was hit by a vehicle. Subsequently, the police on the control of Zhang and criminal detention.

During the court's evidence phase, prosecutors cited Public Security Bureau video, witness statements, victim statements, and the defendant's confession, confirming that during the roughly hour long dispute, zhang always claimed not to be aware of the regulations on body temperature monitoring, and asked security guards and police to show relevant municipal documents, "even if my body temperature exceeds 39 degrees, why should I not be allowed to enter the community? "

According to the Public Prosecutor, the defendant in the case, surnamed Zhang, violently charged a police officer, and according to article two hundred and seventy-seven (1) and (5) of the Criminal Law of the People's Republic of China, his actions constituted a Obstruction of justice, it is recommended that the sentence be imprisonment for a term not exceeding six months and not exceeding eight months.

"The prevention and control of the epidemic may hinder the convenience of individual life, but at the moment of the epidemic, the interests of individuals, the interests of the collective and the interests of the state are one and the failure of individual-level epidemic prevention may lead to the infection of groups and even endanger national security. All the apparent inconveniences in life today are effective ways that ordinary people can take to protect their families, themselves and others. Each person's self-awareness and commitment will help win the battle against the epidemic at an early date,"the prosecutor added.

During the on-court defense, the defense said that the core focus of the dispute between the defendant and the security guard and the police was whether there was a legal and regulatory basis for not being allowed to enter the community due to excessive body temperature. "It is a well-known fact that when an administrative punishment or restriction of personal freedom is carried out, the relevant law enforcement grounds should generally be informed, " the defense said. The case took place on Feb. 9, the notice of the Shanghai Municipal People's Government on the further strict implementation of various epidemic prevention and control measures was released on February 10 and notified the public through the Shanghai announcement on February 11.

In addition, the defense claimed that Zhang accidentally stepped on the accelerator and caused the vehicle to flee while the police were putting their hands into the cab to forcibly pull it out, and brake the vehicle in time to take remedial measures to prevent further escalation of the damage, therefore, I hope the court will grant you a lighter sentence.

In the end, the full court of Qingpu District Court, after verifying the facts and evidence of the case and hearing the views of the parties, said that after the trial, it was found that the defendant's conduct constituted a Obstruction of justice. The court, considering the circumstances of the defendant's confession and Voluntary Confession, sentenced the defendant Zhang to eight months'imprisonment.
